Package: pkgrescue
Type: Package
Title: One-Function Automatic Resolution and Installation of R Packages
Version: 0.2.0
Authors@R:
    person(
      given = "Quentin",
      family = "Lamboley",
      email = "q.lamboley78@gmail.com",
      role = c("aut", "cre")
    )
Description: Resolves and installs an R package from a single call to
    install_any(). The package first recognises installed packages, CRAN,
    Bioconductor, the official R-INLA repository, R-universe, public GitHub,
    public GitLab, package URLs and local sources. It automatically creates a
    writable user library, reuses an already configured system proxy before
    trying a direct connection, tries multiple download methods and CRAN
    mirrors, uses 'pak', 'remotes', 'BiocManager', base R and 'R CMD INSTALL'
    when appropriate, preserves a complete report, and validates the target
    namespace in a clean R process. It never embeds a proxy, stores tokens, or
    runs privileged operating-system commands. External constraints such as
    missing permissions, private repositories, unavailable hosts,
    incompatible R versions, and absent system compilers are reported clearly.
